                        },
                        "displayName": "Joris Van den Bossche",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Brussels"
                    },
                    "body": "{quote}Note that pandas' `take` is a bit complicated by trying to satisfy two APIs simultaneously. \r\n[...]\r\nAnd then there's the \"pandas\" style `take` where `-1` means \"indicator for missing values, which should be filled with the `na_value` parameter.\" Other negative numbers are not allowed.{quote}\r\n\r\nI think this distinction in Arrow is less relevant / easier to deal with. The indices can also have nulls, resulting of nulls in the returned array. This basically takes the role of the -1 in the \"pandas style\" take.\r\n\r\n(working on the Array part in ARROW-5291 /  https://github.com/apache/arrow/pull/4281)",
